HEADWORD: Shealing
<hw>Sheal"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The outer husk, pod, or shell, as
of oats, pease, etc.; sheal; shell.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

